guide.environmentaltech.modifier_piezo.e: Allows solar panels to generate energy from vibrations caused by weather.
guide.environmentaltech.assembler.page.t: The assembler is the primary tool for assembling multiblock machines from Environmental Tech. This will automatically assemble your multiblock machines provided you have the correct blocks in your inventory.
guide.environmentaltech.assembler.page.u: 1. Hold or spam Right click on controllers to assemble multiblocks.
2. Shift + Right click breaks any multiblock block in survival.
3. Shift + Right click controller breaks full multiblock in creative.
4. Left click controller for list of required blocks for multiblock.
guide.environmentaltech.modifiers.page.t: Modifiers are blocks used to upgrade/modify a multiblock. By default every multiblock can support any modifier, but they won't nessesarily have an effect on that particular machine.
guide.environmentaltech.structure_blocks: Structure blocks are the main blocks used in multiblock machines. Structure Frames are usually used as the frame of the machine and Structure Panels are usually used in the sides of machines.
guide.environmentaltech.lightning_rods.p: Lightning Rods allow you to harness the power of lightning! When a lightning bolt hits the rod it generates a large burst of energy.
guide.environmentaltech.solar_arrays.pag:
Solar Arrays allow you to harness the power of the sun! They are great in the sun but are effected by weather and will not generate during the night. 
guide.environmentaltech.solar_arrays.page.text
The Void Miners laser core must have sight to the void or bedrock.
guide.environmentaltech.void_ore_miner.p: Void Ore Miners mine ore from the void. These miners can use large ammounts of energy when modifiers are installed so be sure to provide a decent amount of energy.
guide.environmentaltech.void_res_miner.p: Void Resource Miners mine resources from the void. These resources are typically found in world gen or are used to create other decorative blocks. These miners can use large ammounts of energy when modifiers are installed so be sure to provide a decent amount of energy.
guide.environmentaltech.void_botanic_min: Void Botanic Miners mine from the void. These items and blocks are usually from nature or can be grown. These miners only use a little energy even when using a lot of modifiers.
guide.environmentaltech.nanobot_ranged.p: The Ranged Nanobot Beacon provides players within its range effects that are added with Modifiers. Each effect you add to the beacon will increase the energy cost.
guide.environmentaltech.nanobot.page.chu: The Nanobot Beacon must be chunk loaded if you want the effects wherever you go.
guide.environmentaltech.nanobot_personal: The Personal Nanobot Beacon provides the owner with various effects. Each effect you add to the beacon will increase the energy cost.

gui.environmentaltech.dg.assembler.use1: Hold or spam Right click on controllers to assemble the multiblock.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.assembler.use2: Shift + Right click in survival will instant break any multiblock block and in creative it will instantly destroy the whole multiblock.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.assembler.use3: Left click on any controller to be given a list of all the required blocks for the multiblock structure.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.lightningrod.ab: The lightning rod is a multiblock generator that generates energy from lightning strikes during thunder storms.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.lightningrod.re: Tip of lightning rod must see sky.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.lonsdaleite.abo: Lonsdaleite is a very strong material that can be used to build wither cages. This can be obtained by using the Void Ore Miner.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.mica.about: Mica is a useful crystal used in modifiers and the higher tiers of machines. This can be obtained by using the Void Resource Miner.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.solararray.abou: The solar array is a multiblock generator that generates energy from the sun.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.solararray.req1: Any block above any of the solar cells must allow sunlight through.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.solararray.modi: Allows solar panel to generate energy from the vibrations caused by rain.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.voidoreminer.ab: The void ore miner is a multiblock machine that mines ore from the void at a cost of large amounts of energy. The Lens can be colored to target different resources. Any Modifier can be used in place of the Modifier Cores.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.voidminer.req1: The bottom Laser Core must be able to see bedrock. Any block below Laser Core must let light through.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.voidresminer.ab: The void resource miner is a multiblock machine that mines common resources from the void at a cost of energy. The Lens can be colored to target different resources. Any Modifier can be used in place of the Modifier Cores.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.nanobotbeacon.a: The Nano Bot Beacon is a multiblock machine that provides the player with effects through wireless nano bot technology. The Effects are only applied to the player that placed the Nano Bot Beacon.
gui.environmentaltech.dg.nanobotbeacon.r: Chunkloading if effects are wanted anywhere you go.
